    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. so basically if i accidentally leak something or if my team messes up, im on the hook for their legal fees and anything else they lose? that sounds pretty risky. are there any specific \"red flags\" or hidden ways this clause can be used against me that i should look out for in the wording?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, that's the general idea. As for red flags, be wary of clauses that use language like \"arising out of or occurring in connection with any breach\" or \"negligence or willful misconduct.\" These phrases can be broad and allow the Disclosing Party to claim damages for even minor mistakes.\n\nAlso, look out for clauses that use phrases like \"of whatever kind\" or \"including reasonable attorneys' fees.\" These phrases can be used to capture a wide range of potential damages, and may not be limited to just the costs associated with defending the lawsuit.\n\nIt's also worth noting that this clause can be used to punish you for mistakes or accidents, even if they were unintentional. So, it's essential to read the clause carefully and consider seeking advice from a lawyer or a trusted expert before signing any agreement.",
